  <title>WebKit2.Settings.enable_spatial_navigation</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
Settings.enable_spatial_navigation: Boolean (Read / Write / Construct)
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Whether to enable Spatial Navigation. This feature consists in the ability
to navigate between focusable elements in a Web page, such as hyperlinks
and form controls, by using Left, Right, Up and Down arrow keys.
For example, if an user presses the Right key, heuristics determine whether
there is an element they might be trying to reach towards the right, and if
there are multiple elements, which element they probably wants.</p>
  <p>Since 2.3</p>
